But I didn’t go into politics to do that.
Since joining the Labour Party 32 years ago as a schoolteacher, spurred by the Thatcher government’s neglect that literally left my state high school behind, I have been fighting for better public services for those who need it most – either as a local councillor or government minister.
I never hid my politics, even at the last election.
No one in Nottingham East could have been confused about my policies and areas where I differ from the current leadership.
To those who supported the motion on Friday, I can only say that with the country embarking on a Brexit that is going to harm all households, businesses and our public services, I do not understand the desire to waste time and energy on my loyalty to the Labour Party leader.
